CVEA has started sharing and training sessions on guidelines and standards of valuation in order to strengthen the capacity and develop professional skills to all members of CVEA.

Mr. Kong Vanda, Head of Valuation of POINTER , has gained more than 10 years of evaluation experience and has been trained in valuation skills with international institutions such as RICS and IVSC.
IVS recognized as a global framework for providing policies, guidelines and best practices for the valuation of various types of assets, including real estate, businesses and financial instruments.

The IVS framework is designed to promote consistency, transparency and reliability in valuations conducted around the world and common set of standards for valuers and stakeholders involved in the valuation process. The primary goal is to enhance the credibility and reliability of valuaitons, making tem useful for decision-making.
